Configure terraform so it can connect with azure
------------------------------------------------
1- sign up with azure account
2- Configure VScode -install extensions
    - Bracket pair color DLW
    - Azure terraform
    - Hashicorp terraform
    - Git extension pack
    - Terraform azure autocomplete
    - Azure cli tools
3- https://learn.microsoft.com/cli/azure/install-azure-cli
   - az login //Browser opens → sign in
   - az account set --subscription "SUBSCRIPTION_NAME"
4- Authenticate Using Service Principal (For Automation / CI/CD)
  - create service principal
      az ad sp create-for-rbac --name my-sp --role Contributor --scopes /subscriptions/<SUB_ID>
      You’ll get:
        clientId
        clientSecret
        tenantId
  - Login Using Service Principal
        az login --service-principal -u <clientId> -p <clientSecret> --tenant <tenantId>
5- Authenticate Using environment variable  and restart VScode 
    From Windows powershell
    $env:AZURE_CLIENT_ID="xxxxxxxx-xxxx"
    $env:AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET="xxxxxxxx"
    $env:AZURE_TENANT_ID="xxxxxxxx-xxxx"
    $env:AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID="xxxxxxxx-xxxx"
    From Linux
    export AZURE_CLIENT_ID="xxxxxxxx-xxxx"
    export AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET="xxxxxxxx"
    export AZURE_TENANT_ID="xxxxxxxx-xxxx"
    export AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID="xxxxxxxx-xxxx"

   
